-- Canon Marketing, Fujikura, JSR, Misumi, Nippon Sharyo, THK: Japan Stocks
-- Norie Kuboyama
-- 2010-07-27T06:51:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-27/canon-marketing-fujikura-jsr-misumi-nippon-sharyo-thk-japan-stocks.html

          
          
             Japan’s  Nikkei 225 Stock Average 
fell 6.81, or 0.1 percent, to 9,496.85 as of the close of
trading in Tokyo. The following were among the most active
shares in the Japanese  market  today. Stock symbols are in
parentheses after company names.  
 Canon Marketing Japan Inc.  (8060 JT) tumbled 6.1 percent to
1,226 yen, its biggest decline since June 2009. The company,
which distributes all of  Canon Inc. ’s (7751 JT) products, said
half-year operating profit was 2.87 billion yen for the period
ended June 30, compared with 3.66 billion yen a year earlier.
Canon fell 0.4 percent to 3,515 yen.  
 Fujikura Ltd.  (5803 JT) advanced 2.8 percent to 410 yen.
The cable maker was rated “buy” by  Atsushi Yamaguchi , an
analyst at UBS AG, after the brokerage suspended coverage of
Fujikura on June 22. The share price estimate was set at 500 yen.  
 JSR Corp.  (4185 JT) lost 5 percent to 1,511 yen. The maker
of synthetic resin’s share-price estimate was reduced to 2,100
yen from 2,400 yen by  Nobuhito Owaki , an analyst at JPMorgan
Chase & Co.  
 Misumi Group Inc.  (9962 JT) slumped 5.1 percent to 1,671
yen, the biggest decline since April 2009.  THK Co.  (6481 JT)
declined 6.5 percent to 1,701 yen. The machinery makers were
reduced to “neutral” from “buy” by  Katsushi Saito , an
analyst at Nomura Holdings Inc.  
 Nippon Sharyo Ltd.  (7102 JT) surged 9.5 percent to 393 yen,
the most since Dec. 11. Japan’s biggest maker of high-speed
trains said net income for the quarter ended June 30 was 855
million yen, 51 percent more than a year earlier.  
 Nippon Shinyaku Co.  (4516 JT) gained 4.8 percent to 1,042
yen, the most since Jan. 4. The maker of pharmaceuticals and
health food was rated “strong outperform” in new coverage by
 Toshiyuki Hibino , an analyst at Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley
Securities Co. The share price target was set at 1,400 yen.  
 Seiko Epson Corp.  (6724 JT) increased 4.4 percent to 1,156
yen. The maker of printers may have posted its first group
operating profit in two years in the quarter ended in June
because of increased demand for printers and electronic parts,
Nikkei English News reported.  
 Sumitomo Mitsui Financial Group Inc. (8316 JT) rose 2.8
percent to 2,587 yen. Nikko Cordial Securities Inc., the
investment-banking unit of Sumitomo Mitsui, said first-quarter
profit rose 24 percent on higher commissions and trading
activity.  
 Yokogawa Electric Corp.  (6841 JT) dropped 2.4 percent to
526 yen. The maker of electronic measuring tools had its share
price estimate reduced to 500 yen from 790 yen by  Yukihiko Shimada , an analyst at Mitsubishi UFJ Morgan Stanley Securities
Co.  
